All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddPartController
    The AddPartController provides the control logic supporting the AddPart.fxml scene.
    AddProductController
    The AddProductController provides the control logic supporting the AddProduct.fxml scene.
    InHouse
    The InHouse class describes parts that are manufactured within the company.
    Inventory
    The Inventory class contains static data objects that hold all the existing parts and products.
    Main
    The Inventory Management program manages an inventory of parts and products.
    MainMenuController
    The MainMenuController provides the control logic supporting the MainMenu.fxml scene.
    ModifyPartController
    The ModifyPartController provides the control logic supporting the ModifyPart.fxml scene.
    ModifyProductController
    The ModifyProductController provides the control logic supporting the ModifyProduct.fxml scene.
    Outsourced
    The Outsourced class describes parts that must be sourced from an external company.
    Part  
    Product
    The Product class describes products that consist of associated parts.
    Sanitization
    The Sanitization class is used to sanitize any input that will be used to create or update Part and Product objects.
